criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. 3 or more than 3 embryo implantation failure histories previously (or the number of
             high-quality embryos transplanted is >4);

          2. Age <40 years；

          3. Ultrasound or HSG showed normal uterine cavity, endometrium on transplantation day is
             ≥ 8mm;

          4. There's at least one good quality embryo on transplantation day.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients using donor sperm or donor eggs;

          2. Patients have obvious uterine cavity abnormalities;

          3. There was a clear hydrosalpinx;

          4. Natural cycles or IVM patients;

          5. Patients who cancel the due to the transfer due to various reasons, such as the
             failure of fertilization, or ovarian transitional stimulus syndrome (OHSS);

          6. Abnormal karyotype;

          7. Blastocyst transplantation patients.
